<paragraph id="614EC737AA2A945BFF30FD1DFCF2FB53" blockId="3.[177,1086,654,1145]" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">
C o m m e n t s: This species was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="A6F1BCB4AA2A945BFD5CFD1DFEFEFDEB" authority="(LEPELETIER DE SAINT FARGEAU)" baseAuthorityName="LEPELETIER DE SAINT FARGEAU" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Amegilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albigena">
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFD5CFD1DFD08FD8E" box="[734,749,654,676]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFD79FD1DFCB6FD8E" box="[763,851,654,676]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">albigena</emphasis>
(LEPELETIER DE SAINT FARGEAU)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="0560BAC6AA2A945BFECAFD3FFE29FDE8" author="KOHL F" box="[328,460,684,706]" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" pagination="169 - 301" refId="ref2666" refString="KOHL F. F. (1907): Zoologische Ergebnisse der Expedition der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften nach Sudarabien und Sokotra im Jahre 1898 - 1899: Hymenopteren. - Denkschr. K. Akad. Wiss. [Wien], Math. - Naturwiss. Kl. 71 (1): 169 - 301." type="journal article" year="1907">KOHL (1907</bibRefCitation>
: p. 173), a decision followed by 
<bibRefCitation id="0560BAC6AA2A945BFCADFD3FFC31FDE8" author="BROOKS R" box="[815,980,684,706]" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" pagination="436 - 575" refId="ref2501" refString="BROOKS R. W. (1988): Systematics and phylogeny of the anthophorine bees (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae; Anthophorini). - Univ. Kansas Sci. Bull. 53 (9): 436 - 575." type="journal article" year="1988">BROOKS (1988)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="A6F1BCB4AA2A945BFC63FD3FFEEFFDF5" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Amegilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albigena">
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFC63FD3FFEEFFDF5" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">Amegilla albigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was established by 
<bibRefCitation id="0560BAC6AA2A945BFE64FD59FC64FDF5" author="LEPELETIER DE SAINT FARGEAU A" box="[486,897,713,735]" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" refId="ref2725" refString="LEPELETIER DE SAINT FARGEAU A. L. M. (1841): Histoire naturelle des Insectes - Hymenopteres [vol. 2]. Roret, Paris, 680 pp." type="book" year="1841">LEPELETIER DE SAINT FARGEAU (1841)</bibRefCitation>
for specimens of both sexes from the surroundings of Lyon and 
<collectingCountry id="19E687A7AA2A945BFD20FD75FD32FDD6" box="[674,727,742,764]" name="Algeria" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">Oran</collectingCountry>
, sent by his son, and from Sicily, received from Alexandre Lefébure. 
<bibRefCitation id="0560BAC6AA2A945BFDA4FC97FD23FC30" author="BROOKS R" box="[550,710,772,794]" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" pagination="436 - 575" refId="ref2501" refString="BROOKS R. W. (1988): Systematics and phylogeny of the anthophorine bees (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae; Anthophorini). - Univ. Kansas Sci. Bull. 53 (9): 436 - 575." type="journal article" year="1988">BROOKS (1988)</bibRefCitation>
designated as 
<typeStatus id="BE4A7995AA2A945BFCE0FC97FC5AFC30" box="[866,959,772,794]" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">lectotype</typeStatus>
a female in the Museum National d’Histoire Naturelle a female labeled in an unknown hand only as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="A6F1BCB4AA2A945BFF3EFCADFED6FC7E" box="[188,307,830,852]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Amegilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albigena">
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFF3EFCADFF2EFC7E" box="[188,203,830,852]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFF59FCADFED6FC7E" box="[219,307,830,852]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">albigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; and without actual locality data but presumed to have come from Lyon. This designation is unfortunate given that definitive 
<typeStatus id="BE4A7995AA2A945BFD4BFCCFFCC7FC5B" box="[713,802,860,881]" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">syntypes</typeStatus>
from southern 
<collectingCountry id="19E687A7AA2A945BFC3DFCCFFBE1FC5B" box="[959,1028,860,881]" name="France" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">France</collectingCountry>
of 
<taxonomicName id="A6F1BCB4AA2A945BFBAAFCC8FEEFFCA5" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Amegilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albigena">
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFBAAFCC8FBD2FC5B" box="[1064,1079,859,881]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFF30FCEAFEEFFCA5" box="[178,266,889,911]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">albigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are present in the Hope Entomological Collection, Oxford (vide 
<bibRefCitation id="0560BAC6AA2A945BFC2EFCEAFBD7FCA5" author="BAKER D" box="[940,1074,889,911]" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" pagination="1189 - 1204" refId="ref2448" refString="BAKER D. B. (1994): Type material in the University Museum, Oxford, of bees described by Comte Amedee Lepeletier de Saint-Fargeau and Pierre Andre Latreille (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). - J. Nat. Hist. 28 (5): 1189 - 1204." type="journal article" year="1994">BAKER 1994</bibRefCitation>
). Regardless, the species is polytypic and can be readily confused with various other taxa. Quite contrary to the historical synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="A6F1BCB4AA2A945BFD01FC20FCFCFCE3" authorityName="KIRBY" authorityYear="1900" box="[643,793,947,969]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Amegilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyramidalis">
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFD01FC20FD74FCE3" box="[643,657,947,969]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFD22FC20FCFCFCE3" box="[672,793,947,969]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">pyramidalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the genitalia and concealed sterna are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="A6F1BCB4AA2A945BFE6FFC42FD80FCCC" box="[493,613,977,999]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Amegilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mucorea">
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFE6FFC42FE19FCCD" box="[493,508,977,999]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFD8FFC42FD80FCCC" box="[525,613,977,998]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">mucorea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although the antennae, form of the seventh metasomal sternum, and coloration differ somewhat, and outside of superficial coloration there is no affinity of the former to 
<taxonomicName id="A6F1BCB4AA2A945BFDA7FB98FD7FFB0B" box="[549,666,1035,1057]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Amegilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albigena">
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFDA7FB98FDD6FB0B" box="[549,563,1035,1057]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFDC0FB98FD7FFB0B" box="[578,666,1035,1057]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">albigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The status of 
<taxonomicName id="A6F1BCB4AA2A945BFCB5FB98FC28FB0B" authorityName="KIRBY" authorityYear="1900" box="[823,973,1035,1057]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Amegilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyramidalis">
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFCB5FB98FCA0FB0B" box="[823,837,1035,1057]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFCD6FB98FC28FB0B" box="[852,973,1035,1057]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">pyramidalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in relation to 
<taxonomicName id="A6F1BCB4AA2A945BFF4CFBBBFEA1FB14" box="[206,324,1064,1086]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Amegilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mucorea">
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFF4CFBBBFF38FB14" box="[206,221,1064,1086]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFF6EFBBAFEA1FB14" box="[236,324,1065,1086]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">mucorea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is deserving of further investigation but is herein considered specifically distinct pending a more thorough revision of 
<taxonomicName id="A6F1BCB4AA2A945BFD0FFBD5FD0DFB76" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1897" box="[653,744,1094,1116]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Amegilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFD0FFBD5FD0DFB76" box="[653,744,1094,1116]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">Amegilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="A6F1BCB4AA2A945BFD7AFBD5FC30FB76" authorityName="KIRBY" authorityYear="1900" box="[760,981,1094,1116]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Amegilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="824" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyramidalis">
<emphasis id="53851B25AA2A945BFD7AFBD5FC30FB76" box="[760,981,1094,1116]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">Amegilla pyramidalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<collectingCountry id="19E687A7AA2A945BFE9EFBF0FE8CFB53" box="[284,361,1123,1145]" name="Yemen" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">Socotra</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry id="19E687A7AA2A945BFEF5FBF0FDA4FB53" box="[375,577,1123,1145]" name="Yemen" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">Republic of Yemen</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="A33509D5AA2A945BFDC9FBF0FCEEFB53" box="[587,779,1123,1145]" country="Yemen" name="'Adan" pageId="3" pageNumber="824">Adan Governorate</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
